There are several ways to do this. For example, you could simply use a ternary operator to set an exit label for each iteration.
For example, you could use an if block to check for the number of iterations and set an exit label:
%i=1;
for %i:$loop in 1..$niter do (
    set xlabel "{.}" ; # sets the label in the upper left corner
    %exit=0 ; # exit the loop if it is too high;
    %exit=1 ; # exit the loop if it is too low
    if %i:$loop > %exit then %exit=0             ;
    if %i:$loop <= %exit then %exit=1             ;
)

